Montclair.name: Catf√© Montclair
Montclair.address: 356 Bloomfield Ave #5 SECOND FLOOR WALK UP, Montclair, NJ 07042, USA

text.text: It took everything in me to not apply to adopt all the cats. The place is incredibly clean, they have complimentary coffee/tea, and the cutest babies ever. I was lucky enough to have my party of 3 be the only group in the session, so we got to enjoy the cats all to ourselves. You can tell the cats are well taken care of (healthy coats, vibrant personalities(some are shy, normal!), hydrated, etc). As a cat owner myself, I was very pleased with how the conditions are. And, as a customer, I am very satisfied with the experience!

Had my second visit today and it was just as awesome as the first. The staff is lovely and I just love how you can hang out and watch each cat showcase their personalities from the ones that love playing to ones who stare from a high shelf  (aka calypso lol). Can‚Äôt wait to visit again soon! üíó

For clarification definition of cat cafe: place to pet and play with cats
(Not a cafe with food and drinks and cats in it)

They do offer some complimentary drinks (like Keurig coffee and hot water for tea and hot cocoa) and some for purchase, but if you're looking for a fancy coffee drink, this is not what you're looking for.

Cats are rescues and adoptable. ones that have bonded have to be adopted together. Operation seems very humane.

They do a good job with an intro. The space is small but the air filter works very well. It doesn't smell like a litterbox and after an hour, I (someone with cat allergies) only had a small sniffle which is impressive considering there were 13 cats.

Cats that might be less receptive are clearly marked. Other cats are friendly. They do a good job with rules but don't give much advice for people who haven't spent much time with cats.

They may be over stimulated and are still cats (lightly skittish) so they might gently nip or swat at you if they are not interested in pets.

Arriving: it's on the second floor and you have to continue to traverse some hallways but the door is clearly labeled. Don't get discouraged, just keep going

Tips for people who are not familiar with cats:
1) Don't try to pet a cat that is playing, they'll be wound up and on alert
2) Let the cat sniff you first
3) Petting near the head/ears is normally a better bet, the lower body can be highly stimulating and result in the cat being quickly overstimulated.
4) Move toys with feathers vigorously makes it more interesting for the cat. Move around too.

Mount Laurel Township.name: Four Green Cats Cafe
Mount Laurel Township.address: 118 Creek Rd, Mt Laurel Township, NJ 08054, USA

text.text:
Four Green Cats Cafe - WORTH the wait!

Four Green Cats Caf√© is an absolute gem - a fabulous coffee shop specializing in Czech & European-inspired sweets and savories that are as delightful - unique. My Caramel Latte was perfectly craft, but my latte, amazing as it was, couldn‚Äôt compete with the star of the show: a freshly baked, hot-out-of-the-oven savory doughnut.

This isn‚Äôt your average savory doughnut. It‚Äôs a sweet and savory pastry stuffed with tangy sauerkraut, a slice of sausage, cherry tomato, a sweet pickle slice, and fresh greens. With every bite, my taste buds were intrigued and delighted. The balance of flavors had me wanting to lick my plate!  I didn't : )

The caf√© is cozy and inviting, and the ‚ÄúCats‚Äù (slang for pretty girls and referring to the owner & her family) know their pastries! I managed to resist the German bread pudding and other indulgent sweets, they looked incredible !

Be sure to check out the caf√©‚Äôs history online - there is a wonderful article worth reading. The owner and her family (Cats) have truly created a landmark that‚Äôs just slightly off the beaten path, both physically and in its distinctive cuisine.

SO WHY did I say it was worth the wait?  During the hustling months, the line can be quite long, BUT don't let that deter you!  The wait is worth it for both coffee and authentically created food.  Don‚Äôt miss it‚Äîvisit Four Green Cats Caf√© soon!

A very comfy cafe with comfortable seats and desserts. It is connected to an antique shop which is also good to look around. My wife was bold enough to try Jade Cloud (Jade from Green tea and cloud from milk) which I‚Äôd avoid next visit. Coffee was however good and mild.
Love this place! Their pastries are all phenomenal. We love the Bread pudding, brioche and the donuts. Coffee drinks are great too and staff is always friendly.

cafes.name: Rahway Kitty Hall
cafes.address: 209 W Main St, Rahway, NJ 07065, USA

text.text: Not sure why a couple of recent reviews mentioned bad odor and scratchy cats. We were just there today and had a very pleasant experience - there were many sweet, playful kitties and no bad smells whatsoever. We haven't been to other cat cafes, and while those might be larger, this one was cozy and didn't feel cramped - there was enough space for both the visitors and the cats. All visitors are given disposable shoe covers to keep the place clean - great idea! Please note that the main door is locked, and visitors are let into the reception area in small groups to make sure the cats don't escape. There was a sign set up on the pavement, which we didn't notice, so another one on the door at the eye level would be very helpful. The volunteers were nice, gave us tips on which cats prefer being petted only on the head and answered all our questions. No food or drinks for sale, which is perfectly fine - the main purpose is to enjoy interacting with the adorable kitties and hopefully find a perfect match if you are looking to adopt.

You don‚Äôt buy food here, but you can reserve an hour online, sign a waiver, pay about $10 in person, and play with cats (toys and seats provided)! You are not supposed to pick the cats up. Parking is mostly street parking with meters/app. Second time coming with friends, and I love it! Friendly staff and fellow patrons!

I went here to pet the kittens and play with them. Upon entering, an almost unbearable smell. This place wasn't the cleanest. They offered a few toys and it was fun to play but most the cats were mean and we're biting and scratching. Please keep this place cleaner and let people know if the cats are friendly or not, I got scratched multiple times!!

Had the best time with the kitties. They are everywhere and they love treats.
Getting there was super easy as well as the process to check in. Half an hour is enough time to go around give them some pets and maybe find one to play with for a bit if you are not planning on taking any home (tho I can assure you it‚Äôs super hard not to).
They also have üê∞
Wonderful experience!

Very cute spot and a lovely place to spend some time with their cats and kittens. Cats are up for adoption and there is an approval process. I would recommend reserving your tickets ahead of time if you can because it seems they‚Äôre strict on the entry and exit times. You have 30 minute sessions.

I wouldn‚Äôt call it a cafe since they don‚Äôt really make drinks but you can buy bottled water or coffee. Love the atmosphere and their cats are so sweet and playful.

Great cat cafe. They don‚Äôt really have a large selection of food or snacks so not much of a cafe but still a great experience. The cats are calm and like to be pet. Staff is super nice. Give them a try!

Unknown City.name: Cute Cat Cafe
Unknown City.address: 6669 Fresh Pond Rd, Ridgewood, NY 11385, USA

text.text:
June 2024: While looking for a new coffee place to go to while working on computer I decided on CCC.
Good reviews and lots of tables. Took a chance and glad I did. Will definitely be back! The one thing to note, they do not have AC. Their back and front doors were open and they have fans and today was warm but inside it was comfortable.
So if you must have AC, it won't be available here.
The women behind the counter today were super nice and brought my bagel to me. Nice touch.
Highly recommend this little coffee shop.

It‚Äôs a shame that i have overlooked this place for so long , but i finally gave it a chance and this cute cat cafe is now my go to for coffee. The ladies are always sweet and welcoming, great atmosphere. Their decor is one of my favorites to look at. From a board of customers‚Äô napkin art to cat pictures. Their coffee is always delicious, it‚Äôs always fresh, and the best flavor ü©∑

This coffee shop is awesome! It has great food, great service, and a friendly atmosphere. There is plenty of seating both inside and out and seems like an awesome place to do some work. The maple iced latte I had tasted really unique and I would recommend checking it out. If for nothing less than to try something new.

This is my favorite shop in the area. Super unpretentious and simple - exactly what i feel most people want early in the morning. Excellent coffee quality and atmosphere.

Hands down one of the best if not the best customer service in coffee I have ever experienced. The barista/ people that work there was so friendly and welcoming it made the drink much more enjoybale.

Just look at the leaf on the latte 6/5 stars

Just a nice little neighborhood spot to grab some great coffee with awesome service. The staff here is super nice. Their iPad was down this morning so they couldn't process payments. They gave us our coffee and pastries, and told us to ‚Äúcome back and pay tomorrow. I just wanna make sure you get your coffee.‚Äù So nice!
Free coffee when you buy a bag of beans! Very nice service

It‚Äôs a cute place only because of the claw machines, the lighting, and the cute ice cream. The service was very slow. It was just me and my husband inside the cafe. We only ordered 3 items - a mango slush, a watermelon slush, and a teddy bear mousse. It took about 15-20 minutes just to get our drinks. Add an additional 20 for the small bear mousse cake. All 3 items cost roughly $25. The little mousse cake, which could‚Äôve been devoured in 2 bites by a man was $9. I‚Äôve had better mango slush from other bubble tea places. The watermelon slush wasn‚Äôt bad. I believe they may have used real watermelon. In any case, I probably would not revisit, but it‚Äôs a great attraction spot for little ones. Be prepared to dish out money.
Such a cute little cafe for enjoying some boba and dessert. Super great lighting for fantastic looking photos. Claw machines is a nice touch. Hard to win prizes though but that‚Äôs expected.

Came here with my nephew + partner + family. It was a cute little spot with tea and claw games! The tea was pretty delicious and the claw games are very fun for those who like claw games (my partner) to enjoy.
Best cat lounge we've been to! We had a very pleasant and calming experience visiting the lounge and playing with kittens. You also can feed them with treats. Will come back :)
Cute little space with adoptable cats you can visit for a very fair price. Met the founder and you could tell how much love and dedication is put into this place. Great vibes all around!
Good Home helped me foster and adopt my two cats and couldn‚Äôt be more supportive, responsive, and compassionate! I would highly recommend them as a foster or potential cat parent!!!

Doylestown.name: MeWow Cat Cafe
Doylestown.address: 3617 Old Easton Rd, Doylestown, PA 18902, USA

text.text:
I happen to be googling something else. Another brick and mortar business but this caught my eye and was surprised there was a cat cafe nearby us!!

This is unusual for me to give 4 stars.

I took one less star because they don‚Äôt want any kids under 5. Their rule and I had leave my 3 year old son at home rather than enjoying this cat cafe experience with his big brother.

Place is kept clean. Friendly, one in particular who was very nice.

I didn‚Äôt catch their names as they were not wearing one

Tea, coffee or any snacks are not part of the ticket when you get into their kitty coral

Would i come back again‚Ä¶? Most likely not

Otherwise, the cat experience satisfied my son to play with their cats for 25 minutes.

It is highly recommended to book your cat experience through their website. It does have a fee to book it and they would charge credit card processing fee if you were to purchase something in store.

We only book the 25 minutes and here is what I‚Äôve paid for

It‚Äôs $10 per adult
$7 for children 5-12 year old

This was our first time here, and I LOVED it!! Such a cute little place, and the employees were very nice! The cats were ADORABLE, I wanted to take them home! But alas, I already have 4 üòî (although what's one more?). All the stuff they had to buy was perfect for cats and cat lovers alike, and the treats and drinks were delicious! I can't wait to come back ü•∞üíï

Always love visiting the kittens and cats!!  Everyone who works there are so incredible and so sweet w. All the cats!!! I help out with Kitty Junction who of the rescues there and mewow cafe is THE best place to visit!!! I stopped over today in fact and loved snuggling with thr kittens!!

Had the best time with the cats here at Whiskers! The owners/workers are gems of people who are just so kind and want you to be comfortable and meet all the babies. They are dedicated to the cats in their care and are quite laid back.
The kitten room was fun but was hard to enjoy due to the smell. The room does not get circulation so there is a very overwhelming litter smell. That can probably be aided with air purifiers and litter deodorizer. Overall I enjoyed my visit, will likely be back, and will be recommending to others!

The owner is incredibly sweet, with stories about each cat that shows she is invested in the future of them all. Sweeter than her are the cats themselves! They are very friendly to humans. If you're ever looking to adopt a cat, I would highly recommend this place

Tim and Lina are so sweet!! They introduced us to each cat and kitten and offered comfort & beverages. They made the cafe feel like a familiar home. All the cats were so sweet and adorable. Definitely a place to visit to de-stress if you love cats.

Philadelphia.name: Le Cat Cafe
Philadelphia.address: 2713 W Girard Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19130, USA

text.text:
Well, this was a first for me. My daughter loves cats, so we went to a cat cafe. A very interesting place, they bring in stray cats off the streets and give them a place to stay, hoping to be adopted. They are cleaned, tested, vaccinated, and spayed/neutered.
The cafe looks like a playground for cats, with toys and platforms all over for the cats to entertain themselves.
The cafe also offers free coffee/tea, hot cocoa and other drinks to enjoy while you keep the cats company.
All the cats are up for adoption or to foster. In 2024 alone, they had gotten over 350 cats adopted! It was a fun time, especially watching my daughter‚Äôs heart melt while the 10+ cats in this place scurried around and played!

had a nice time at this cafe. so many cats with different personalities, it was nice to get to know some of them a bit. the workers knew a lot about each cat and were really helpful in their explanation. they were also really friendly which is always a plus. i just came for the vibes, though i would potentially be open to adopting a cat in the right timing. i do wish they had non-caffeinated tea which was the only down side for me. will likely return. üíó

This place goes above and beyond to help find loving homes for cats. I adopted a cat from there in 2019 and renamed him Alamo. All the cats in the cafe are available for adoption and even if someone is not looking to adopt, they can come and play with cats while sipping coffee. Bree, one of the ladies that works there was so friendly and told us about all the cats; their names and personalities. She also listened while I told her about my cat. This place is amazing!

Family brunch at a small cafe in Devon. I have to admit I was kind of freaked out when we arrived and they had a number of cats in crates near the front door. But I have come to learn that this is a non-profit operation where all the proceeds benefit the needs of homeless, abandoned, injured and sick cats and kittens.  Wow! They were very accommodating to us when we had to keep changing our reservation. Kudos to them!!!  The actual food was just okay.  My home fries were burned.  My French toast was mildly tasty.  The creamed chipped beef had a very odd flavor (too eggy or too much uncooked flour).  Nothing was extraordinary, but I applaud the cause.

Phenomenal! The food was incredible. Had the bacon, tomato and grilled cheese sandwich. Service was very accommodating because two minutes after we were sat we found out our next appointment moved up and they quickly changed our order to- go and had us on our way. And of course the cats were adorable.

Excellent service: attentive, thorough, and accommodating with recommendations and options. By far the best chip beef I‚Äôve been served, the custom omelette was perfect and the sourdough toast it came with was fresh, flavorful and perfectly toasted. If you like scrapple, they cook it to absolute perfection. Pan seared, not deep fried, as it should be. üòÆ‚Äçüí®ü§å
10/10 would recommend and come back!!

cafes.name: Fat Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 801 E 8th St, Ocean City, NJ 08226, USA

text.text: Pastries are phenomenal!!! Everything is soft and fresh! Will definitely be back!!!!
By far some of the best cookies and pastries I have had in my life!

New York.name: Koneko
New York.address: 26 Clinton St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text: Amazing little experience where you get to place a brunch order, then play with a bunch of adoptable cats and kittens! After your time is up with the cats, you come back to the cafe and your food is hot and ready. Overall a very chill and fun experience, would totally recommend!

We stop here every time we visit NYC- the coffee is good, but we come for the cats. We're always happy to spend some money to support the adoption of the kitties. Make sure to make a reservation if you want to visit the cats!

Made a quick stop to Koneko Cafe. I ordered an iced strawberry matcha latte and it was better than what I expected, the balance between the sweetness of the strawberry and the matcha was perfect. To experience your coffee in the cattery a reservation is required in advance. Overall 4 star experience.

New York.name: Meow Parlour
New York.address: 43 Essex St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text:
We had so much fun at the Meow Parlour! The cats were so fun and the staff was very friendly. The coffee and pastries were delicious. There is a fun gift shop with so many cat themed goodies. If you‚Äôre looking for a fun and relaxing time hanging out with cats, this is the place for you.

The cat hangout area has a lot of seating as well as tables where you can do some work. You have to take your shoes off before entering the cat area. There is a place to hang coats and place shoes before going in. You can bring your drink and pastries in while you hang out with the cats. Can‚Äôt wait to go back, definitely recommend!

The floor was a little cold but apart from that it was nice. I would recommend wearing some thick socks and enjoy your time in there. The cats are very friendly and taken good care of. We were there at 4 pm and a few cars were asleep which is cool. I loved that the place didn‚Äôt smell and there was a restroom. The staff are nice and there is a little souvenir shop.

It was my first visit to Meow Parlour. Very cool place. I reserved a time online. There were probably 10 people in with me but it‚Äôs a large space/rooms so you have plenty of space to visit with all the cats.

There are many cat toys and cool cat tees and spaces for the cats to chill and nap.l the cats are great. Kittens and older cats. Amazing they all coexist. I love that they are lo available for adoption

There is a store in the front with cat toys, cute stickers, shirts, candles, and anything cat related. The team working the front and in the cat room were friendly and helpful.
I took my two children here and it was an amazing way to spend an hour.  Staff is very attentive and there are plenty of cats to play and pet.  All very sweet and well taken care of

WOW! Came here on a Sunday with the girls and it was the perfect detox from a weekend. I love how the staff made everything clean with hand washing and sanitizer before and after playing, touching the kitties. There is a Cat room and a Kitten room you can hop back and forth from. The cats are super friendly and you are able to play with them using different toys in each room. I also love how they had binders with information on each cat including names, age, etc, in order to really learn about each one !

What a relaxing way to spend an hour! Their new location may have a non descript exterior, but the inside was clean and spacious. Most importantly, its feline residents were well cared for and socialized. We enjoyed both the adult cat & kitten rooms, learning about the cats thanks to their helpful bio binder and the knowledgeable staff. The perfect weekend outing (and place to find a kitty companion).

cafes.name: Cats Luck
cafes.address: 140 Steiner Ave, Neptune City, NJ 07753, USA

text.text:
The first time I came through back in April, I ordered multiple boxes of baked goods for customer visits and received rave reviews from everyone so I knew this was a keeper.

Coming through today for lunch and a pile of sweets to bring home, I very pleased with ny Blueberry Bacon Crunchwrap. Would‚Äôve loved more of the Violife feta throughout but still delicious.

Face it, the journey back to Western MA is a barren wasteland with few vegan bakeries unless you stay along and through northern NJ. CT and Western MA have zippo, zero, niet. That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs especially important to load up!

Cats Luck is an absolutely wonderful place for the plant based community (and the community in general!). Not only do they have wonderful food but their small staff is amazing. They always have a bakery case FULL of some of the most creative and interesting treats, all of which are great. Their apple cider donuts (when they have them) are my favorite donuts I‚Äôve ever had in my life. They have a wide menu of typical American style comfort food and they also often run specials with really cool, innovative additions to the menu for a limited time. The people who work there are great. They are friendly, personable and just downright good people with good hearts it seems. The space itself has limited seating indoors and a handful of picnic tables outdoors to eat your food. They also host events every so often that are always a hit and a nice way to spend time with your community.

What a seriously AMAZING place. Cats Luck has been on my bucket list for awhile & I finally got to visit. This place is a GEM! I‚Äôve been vegan for over a decade & this place is hands down in my top 3 best vegan spots! Cool people, super fun decor, loving & welcoming vibes to ALL - AND amazing mind blowing vegan food!!! They offer a staple menu but always have rotating new things to try. Their dessert selection? Out of this world!!! Delicious! Unique! What we got on our visit:

- vegan chicken & waffles. The BEST! The waffle portion was massive. Super moist, dense & sweet. The perfect waffle completed with super crispy & flavorful fried chicken! It was served with butter, gravy & maple syrup- how perfect.

- a bunch of desserts to go! Their cookies were super moist & delicious. It was Halloween weekend so they had so many adorable Halloween themed treats- including a delicious cake cup with was super cute with orange/black theme with chocolate zombie fingers!

Seriously, come & support this GREAT place! They have amazing vegan breakfast, brunch & lunch offerings as well as to go items & mind blowing vegan desserts you cannot skip! We cannot WAIT to return & become regulars. They had street parking right out front & picnic tables to eat at. They don‚Äôt offer indoor dining.

Vegan or not - come here for banging food, treats & good vibes! üíïüí´

Spring City.name: Craig‚Äôs Cat Cafe
Spring City.address: 11 Riverside Dr, Spring City, PA 19475, USA

text.text: Absolutely the most precious little cafe with such a great cause! They sell coffee, treats & little trinkets where % of proceeds go to rescuing cats lives. Super friendly staff (small business ran by a mother and her two daughters); Cafe and cat area were both very clean, all kittens are up for adoption which is ran through a legit rescue that they partnered up with. Entry fee is $5 (with age restrictions for children & ONLY adults can pick the kittens up - children are not allowed‚Ä¶which I greatly RESPECT them for having these rules in place for the kittens safety). Overall, it was such a cute/pleasant experience and I can‚Äôt wait to bring my cat lover family & friends. Kudos
I can't get enough of this place! It‚Äôs my go-to whenever I need a mood boost or just want to relax. The cats are so friendly and absolutely adorable, making it impossible not to smile! :)

Stopped by on a Sunday afternoon.  We are not newbies to this concept as we are regulars at Cats in Bloom in Bloomsburg PA.

The good:
Cats are clearly well cared for.
The room was the appropriate size for the number of cats.
Cats had access to clean water and food.
Cats had plenty of toys and some safe spaces if they didn‚Äôt want to socialize.

The bad:
I 1000% disagree with the age policy (kids of all ages are allowed).  There were 3 kids there when we arrived (all clearly no more than age 7-8).  Two of them were relentlessly following cats around that clearly didn‚Äôt want to socialize with them.  One cat ‚Äúwarned‚Äù one of the kids multiple times but she didn‚Äôt stop.  Literally all of the cats but 1-2 were in a hiding spot.  Then a mom with FOUR kids walked in (age range was probably 5-10). That‚Äôs when we left.  I just couldn‚Äôt watch these kids stressing the cats out any longer.  Also - this was not a large room and there were now 8 adults and 7 kids in there.

My opinion may not be popular but I dont believe the owner‚Äôs intent is for this to be a petting zoo when it‚Äôs too cold for your kids to go outside.  And I realize an age policy may reduce the number of visitors - I‚Äôd happily spend more on admission to see these cats not have to deal with the stress of young children.

I also think there should be a reservation system or a time limit or some way to cut down on the number of people in that room at one time.  At least at high traffic times.

I really love this concept but there needs to be an age policy and you need more space.  Personally I would get rid of the cafe side and make the whole thing cat visitation.

Had this on my "wanna go to" list, and I'm glad I was able to go. It's a smaller Cafe, but VERY GOOD.  Was pretty busy when we first got there, & felt bad for the woman taking,  filling, & taking the orders to the very full tables. She did have some help show up, shortly after we ordered.  Food was GREAT,  for as busy as it was, it was very clean. Staff was very nice, highly recommend.

Very cute cafe. There‚Äôs a breakfast and lunch menu, along with a small bakery. Breakfast ends at 1pm, and we got there a few minutes after one, but they let us order from the breakfast menu, which was greatly appreciated. The food was good, and the place was clean. Overall, a wonderful experience.

This is my type of place. Was in town from Boston and looking for some coffee and breakfast and found this place where near I was staying!! Super cozy breakfast restaurant vibe inside with local artists work on the walls. I got a great iced latte, a really yummy cheesy bacon egg and cheese on a roll, and an insanely good raspberry crumb cake. Everything came out quickly and I think the prices were good. I want to know the details on the crumb cake because the crumb layer was SO THICK and delicious.

cafes.name: Cat Nook Cafe
cafes.address: 18 W Winona Ave, Norwood, PA 19074, USA

text.text: The cats are so cute and friendly! The cafe is decorated so well and cute! The staff is friendly and very helpful. The merch is worth buying and the cafe is in a great area. Definitely a chill place to forget everything when you're petting cats for an hour! We'll be visiting again.

The Cat Nook Cafe in Norwood is a haven for cat lovers. For just $10 an hour, you can relax and enjoy the company of  10-12 adorable, adoptable cats! The fee goes directly to supporting the organization and the care of these furry friends.

The staff are incredibly friendly and clearly passionate about their feline residents. They're happy to share information about each cat's personality and care, which adds a personal touch.  While the cat area is cozy, it's a clean and comfortable space with plenty of seating for around 6 people.  There are even a few toys available so you can engage and play with the cats!

What's even better is that all the kitties are available for adoption.  They've partnered with a local rescue, giving these furry friends a chance to find their forever homes.

It's the perfect spot to unwind and de-stress with some feline company.  Parking is easy, too, with spots available along the side of the road and a parking area across the street. Highly recommend a visit!

Cute place! Small cafe area where you can buy coffee, tea, and snacks. Cat lounge had around 10 kitties, all very friendly. Less of a cafe; you come for the cats! It was so nice to just hang out and play with them. There are lots of toys and beds for the cats. Couches for the people. They had music on for a nice ambiance. There was a family there at the same time as me, but I didn't mind sharing time with them. I would love to come back soon!
